description: Concatenate first n nonzero Fibonacci numbers in reverse order.
references: Mihaly Bencze [Beneze], L. Tutescu, Some Notions and Questions in Number Theory, Sequence 7.
links: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..96
prog: (Haskell)a038399 n = a038399_list !! (n-1)a038399_list = h "" $ tail a000045_list where   h xs (f:fs) = (read ys :: Integer) : h ys fs     where ys = show f ++ xs-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Mar 01 2014
author: M. I. Petrescu (mipetrescu(AT)yahoo.com)
extensions: More terms from Andrew Gacek (andrew(AT)dgi.net), Feb 21 2000
